      "text": "We believe this to be caused by an upstream provider issue.&lt;/p&gt;</content> </entry> <entry> <id>tag:status.cdnjs.com,2005:Incident/18023256</id> <published>2023-08-04T15:33:04Z</published> <updated>2023-08-04T15:33:04Z</updated> <link rel=\"alternate\" type=\"text/html\" href=\"https://status.cdnjs.com/incidents/j85nrhmbcbc5\"/> <title>SRI hashes changed on multiple libraries</title> <content type=\"html\">&lt;p&gt;&lt;small&gt;Aug &lt;var data-var='date'&gt; 4&lt;/var&gt;, &lt;var data-var='time'&gt;15:33&lt;/var&gt; UTC&lt;/small&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Resolved&lt;/strong&gt; - At this time we believe the fix to restore file content and SRI hashes is working as expected.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;small&gt;Aug &lt;var data-var='date'&gt; 2&lt;/var&gt;, &lt;var data-var='time'&gt;18:26&lt;/var&gt; UTC&lt;/small&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Monitoring&lt;/strong&gt; - A backfill has been completed that is believed to have restored files to their previous states, with the SRI hashes reverted to what they were prior to this incident.",
